{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Completion evidence — single-culprit blame auto-derivation and ambiguous-no-link ARE tested, in the committed companion tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_caused_by_autoderive_heldout.py (held-out-TDD split; both files committed + green in CI #829 Verified+1): test_blame_autoderives_single_culprit (closes a bug --class regression over a single-culprit git fixture -> caused_by link to the resolved ticket, proving the _write_link_event direct-writer defeats the closed-source guard) and test_ambiguous_blame_draws_no_autolink (a >50%-ambiguous two-commit blame draws NO auto caused_by link). The explicit --caused-by path is in the happy file test_caused_by_autoderive.py. The >50% strict-majority threshold is mutation-tested."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784469921890216001,"uuid":"166c76f2-b33c-4afc-9bb4-b33f7dfcc088"}